{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"preodorous-veiny-blobfish","description":"## Why\nBenign-vs-competing HEAD-drift tolerance is only tested by calling the `_drift_is_benign`\nclassifier directly and by two source-inspecting tests: `test_drift_is_benign_helper_exists`\n(pure `hasattr`, VALIDATED redundant — siblings already call the helper) and\n`test_apply_batch_uses_drift_is_benign` (`inspect.getsource` substring wiring check, which\nself-describes as structural). The real `_apply_batch` **continue** path\n(`src/rebar/rebar_reconciler/.../applier.py:556,674,718`) is never driven with an injected\ndrift commit. `tests/.../apply/test_applier_drift.py` drives only the raise path.\n\n## What\nAdd batch-level tests against a real tickets-branch git fixture that inject a HEAD change\nbetween mutations, and remove the two structural tests.\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_apply_batch_drift_tolerance.py`.\n- Keep the direct classifier tests (`test_drift_tolerates_*` / `test_drift_rejects_*`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `test_drift_is_benign_helper_exists` and `test_apply_batch_uses_drift_is_benign`\n      are deleted.\n- [ ] New behavioral tests cover: benign unrelated-ticket commit continues; same-ticket\n      `ticket:` EDIT; `ticket:` DELETE of the targeted ticket; several sequential benign\n      commits; a competing `pass_record:` commit aborts before the next Jira call;\n      subject-lookup failure treated as non-benign; manifest/`mutations_completed` count\n      correct after a mid-pass abort.\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"8111-2c48-257a-44ae","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":2,"tags":["p1","reconciler","change-detector"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Real _apply_batch HEAD-drift behavioral tests; delete the two structural drift tests"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784808030782001,"uuid":"3f7e3e5a-6e57-4a31-9fbf-031ee523e185"}